reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Assembly took a few hours (and I have a LOT of experience assembling furniture), just due to the amount of parts. A couple do the diagrams took a little bit to figure out. Once done, this thing looks great! It feels super sturdy. One important thing- the hinges are adjustable and include directions so you can make the doors fit in just the right positions. The shelves are also adjustable so I can actually fit my large rotisserie in the bottom of one with more room!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Assembly not too bad
reviews.reviewText: As others have said, this takes about a solid 5 hours to assemble, but the directions are straightforward and clear though they are just pictures only. Originally I thought I was missing a part but just needed to read the directions more closely. Adjusting the doors is a pain! I eventually just gave up and will live with the slight gap between one set of doors.Piece looks nice despite the wood not being the best quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Functional But Not Great Quality
reviews.reviewText: This took forever to put together. I did have my older teen daughter help for a little while, then my husband helped some, but it still took about 5 1/2 hours to put together. And the doors are not even and one drawer is wonky. It is fine since we still have little kids in the house that will be using it, so I'd rather not spend a lot of money on something they will probably not take great care of, but overall it looks good in our dining room. I'm using half as a coffee bar and the other side for homeschool storage. It works for what I needed. It does provide a good amount of storage space. I was able to put mugs, syrups, and coffee pods on one side, and plenty of room in the other for all their school and art supplies. I will definitely upgrade at some point, but it does the job for now.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for Coffee Station!
reviews.reviewText: This item is really perfect for us. I took my time assembling it, it took me about 2 hours or so working by myself. Instructions were easy to follow and the smaller assembly parts had extras in case of loosing one which is always a relief. Once it is put together it looks very nice!! It really is perfect for what we needed. The seller was also very helpful, we had an issue with FedEx delivering it to the completely wrong address and the seller kindly shipped us a new one. Excellent all around!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: We ordered two of these to be set up side-by-side for additional kitchen cupboard space. They are beautiful and are perfect size. They are solid but not to heavy to move. The directions were easy to read for assembling them. No missing parts. We had some issues with the 2nd one. It was damaged when we got it. The company was fabulous to work with us and made everything right. Excellent customer service!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: There were mixed reviews but it was just what I wanted so tried it. Not disappointed. If you read the instructions one step at a time, it will go together fine. There is a gap when the doors close that can probably be fixed by adjusting the hinges but because it’s all black, it doesn’t show. It’s beautiful and priced right.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the purchase
reviews.reviewText: Worth what I paid for. Look nice, hid my mess, and functions well. Instructions were on point and not difficult to put together, just took time and focus. I'm pleased!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Product mostly as Described
reviews.reviewText: So here’s my review. I’m a 56 year old female and it was pretty easy to assemble alone. The packaging was fantastic and no damage in shipping even though the outer box was damaged. I love the overall look of the furniture. My don’t likes are the drawers don’t line up great and neither do the doors. I know there is a way to adjust them but I haven’t figured it out. The knobs that were included are a cheap fake gold color not black like shown in the photo. The drawers are narrow, I was planning on putting my table placemats there but they did not fit. I would say the unit feels a bit flimsy but what I put in it is holding. The finish gets damaged very easily especially durning the process of putting it together.
